    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Savannah Ga</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>19 Novr 1859</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose you a chk: for Twelve<lb/> dolls. in full for subscription
                to the<lb/> Occident to <date>March</date> next. I request you<lb/> to sign &amp;
                return the above receipt.<lb/> I think you <hi rend="underline">ought</hi> to
                collect your<lb/> subscriptions annually, which you<lb/> might easily do through
                'Adams' Ex=<lb/>=press. It is due to yourself &amp; to your<lb/> subscribers. Many
                men can afford<lb/> to pay three dolls: who can not<lb/> pay when years have
                accumulated<lb/> the sum to five or $4 times that<lb/> amount. You complain of
                the</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>falling off of the subscribers to your<lb/> periodical &amp; oh how fervently do
                I<lb/> pray that you could see the real<lb/> cause of the decay of religion, and
                of<lb/> interest in Judaism in the <placeName>United<lb/> States</placeName>. In
                this country—practical<lb/> and <hi rend="underline">thinking</hi> as it is, the
                mind<lb/> must be convinced, &amp; it <sic>wont</sic> do<lb/> to tell men, you must
                do thus,<lb/> because your fathers did so, for<lb/> this puts a stop to all progress
                &amp;<lb/> that is against the spirit of the<lb/> age—of every ten Americans,
                who<lb/> are educated, known to me, mine<lb/> are in favor of a thorough change<lb/>
                of Synagogue worship—or service—<lb/> and yet I do not know one who</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>would abrogate one particle of real<lb/> Judaism—they can not be made<lb/> to believe
                that the Religion which<lb/> God gave to his chosen people con=<lb/>=sists of my
                zitzith, Lulab, &amp; shophar”—<lb/> Forms &amp; ceremonies are necessary<lb/> &amp;
                proper, but they are mere<lb/> out works to protect the inner<lb/> jewel, &amp; must
                conform to the<lb/> tables of each succeeding age.<lb/> And what is the
                result—educated<lb/> Jews become disgusted with the<lb/> antiquated forms, &amp;
                keep away<lb/> from Synagogue. But I have<lb/> said more than I intended, &amp;
                only<lb/> in reply to your complaint.<lb/> I love my <hi rend="underline"
                    >Religion</hi>, &amp; I mourn<lb/> over its decay.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yr. Friend &amp; well wisher</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Solomon Cohen</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P.S. Now that I know how my a/c<lb/> stands I will remit annually<lb/>
                <persName role="author">C</persName></p>
        </body>
